<item>
            <title>[SPARK-14402] initcap UDF doesn&apos;t match Hive/Oracle behavior in lowercasing rest of string</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-14402</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Current, SparkSQL `initCap` is using `toTitleCase` function. However, `UTF8String.toTitleCase` implementation changes only the first letter and just copy the other letters: e.g. &lt;b&gt;sParK&lt;/b&gt; --&amp;gt; &lt;b&gt;SParK&lt;/b&gt;. (This is the correct expected implementation of `toTitleCase`.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, The main goal of this issue provides the correct `initCap`.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
