                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15225967" author="srowen" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:32:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Title case just means each word starts with an uppercase letter, or at least, that&apos;s a reasonable definition and seems to be the intent. &quot;this is NewCo&quot; should become &quot;This Is NewCo&quot; not &quot;This Is Newco&quot;, so I don&apos;t think it&apos;s correct to un-capitalize other chars.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15225977" author="apachespark" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:37:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;dongjoon-hyun&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/12175&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/12175&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15225983" author="dongjoon" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:44:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh. that could be possible. Thank you, @srowen. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I found this from SQL `initcap` function difference from Hive.&lt;br/&gt;
Spark uses &apos;toTitleCase` to implement `initcap`, but Hive&apos;s `initcap` SQL function works like that.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Should I make another function for `initcap` then?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15225985" author="srowen" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:48:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oh I see. That&apos;s a more specific and probably legit issue. If the intent is to emulate initcap from Hive then you&apos;re right that this doesn&apos;t behave the same way, since it explicitly promises to un-capitalize the rest of the letters. Maybe retitle this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Are there other usages of toTitleCase? if this is the only one and it&apos;s not fit for purpose, maybe it should be moved out to the code implementing initcap and modified to implement initcap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15225988" author="dongjoon" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:50:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;When I search the code, the only usage of `toTitleCase` is `InitCap`. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15225996" author="dongjoon" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:53:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I will investigate on moving that code. &lt;br/&gt;
I think I can do that tomorrow morning. &lt;br/&gt;
Thank you for your advice!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15226001" author="srowen" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 09:55:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, here&apos;s the Hive reference: &lt;a href=&quot;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/LanguageManual+UDF#LanguageManualUDF-StringFunctions&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/Hive/LanguageManual+UDF#LanguageManualUDF-StringFunctions&lt;/a&gt; and a similar reference about Oracle: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.sqlines.com/oracle/functions/initcap&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.sqlines.com/oracle/functions/initcap&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I assume the goal is to emulate these. I personally would support moving this code to the UDF since toTitleCase is a little bit specific for a general &quot;string&quot; class and only used for this UDF, which it doesn&apos;t quite implement correctly.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15226381" author="dongjoon" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 14:40:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you so much, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=srowen&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;srowen&quot;&gt;srowen&lt;/a&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15227083" author="marmbrus" created="Tue, 5 Apr 2016 20:31:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Issue resolved by pull request 12175&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/12175&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/12175&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15227536" author="apachespark" created="Wed, 6 Apr 2016 01:39:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;User &apos;jaceklaskowski&apos; has created a pull request for this issue:&lt;br/&gt;
